cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on Wireless Sensor Networks and their integration into the Internet of Things. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses data reduction techniques. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of prediction methods to support WSNs' growth. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as WSNs are a type of distributed computing system. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch on security concerns related to data transmission in WSNs.
